  "title": "Sales Executive (Lubricant Industry)",
  "description": "<p><u>Responsibilities </u></p><ul><li>Product Mastery: Learn and understand the features, uses, and technical aspects of various fuel & lubricant products.</li><li>Sales Canvassing: Engage in door-to-door or field sales to approach potential clients directly.</li><li>Client Acquisition & Retention: Create and execute marketing strategies to attract new customers and retain existing ones.</li><li>Sales Tracking: Maintain accurate records using the company’s pipeline management tools.</li><li>Target Achievement: Meet or exceed monthly, quarterly, and annual sales goals.</li><li>Cross-functional Collaboration: Work with other teams to ensure excellent customer experience and operational efficiency.</li><li>Credit Management: Monitor and ensure clients follow agreed credit terms</li></ul><p><u>Requirements</u></p><ul><li>No prior experience needed – training will be provided.</li><li>Strong people skills and clear communication abilities.</li><li>Self-motivated and target-oriented mindset.</li><li>Quick learner with technical curiosity.</li><li>Good negotiation skills and a team-oriented approach.</li><li>5-day work week. </li></ul><p>EA Personnel Name: Tan Wei Wen<br />EA Personnel No: R25145042<br />EA License No: 95C5411</p>",
